        <abstract> 
<p>Received JDD’s book [<hi rend="italic">Manual of geology</hi> (1862)]</p>  
<p>and pamphlet on man ["On the higher subdivisions in the classification of mammals", <hi rend="italic">Am. J. Sci.</hi> 2d ser. 35 (1863): 65–71].</p> 
            <p>Fully admits JDD’s objections are valid. But is convinced of the general truth of his own views (with much incidental error), because they embrace so many phenomena and explain them.</p>
            <p>Discusses some mistakes Owen has made;</p> 
<p>Falconer’s disagreement with Owen ["On the mammalian genus Plagiaulax", <hi rend="italic">Q. J. Geol. Soc. Lond.</hi> 18 (1862): 348–69].</p> 
        </abstract>
